President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Johnathan Bragg and Thomas Jayne to key positions in his administration. Bragg, from Virginia, is being nominated as a Member of the Railroad Retirement Board as Employee Representative for the remainder of a five-year term expiring in 2019, and an additional five-year term expiring in 2024. He currently serves as the National Vice President for the Brotherhood of Railroad Signalmen and has held various national offices within the union. Bragg has extensive experience and understanding of the needs of rail workers, retirees, and their families. Jayne, from Missouri, is being nominated as a Member of the Railroad Retirement Board as Carrier Representative for the reminder of a five-year term expiring in 2023. He has been a senior general attorney with BNSF Railway Company since 2011 and has worked on legal and regulatory matters for multiple Class I railroads. Jayne has also worked with the Railroad Retirement Board on issues related to railroad law and taxation. He is a graduate of Westminster College and the University of Missouri School of Law.